{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"87036e0d-b47f-4972-82b3-baf442219e29","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference types from files listed *before* them. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but `Domain.fs` is listed second.\n\nFixing by swapping the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_017Bc3J4Y1BCJ2m2LBTR17jK","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-0a4875968c1947b1a3f66b72d3ea7f6d/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-0a4875968c1947b1a3f66b72d3ea7f6d/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"7d211cd2-589f-49e5-8d18-52ddc60c562e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file compilation order matters — files can only reference types/modules defined in files listed *before* them in the `.fsproj`. \n\nCurrently the order is:\n1. Services.fs (uses Domain types)\n2. Domain.fs (defines Domain types)\n3. Program.fs\n\n`Services.fs` references `BrokenOrder.Domain`, but `Domain.fs` comes after it. The fix is to swap the order so `Domain.fs` comes before `Services.fs`.","outputTokens":372,"requestId":"4429:22827A:169E676:19B29BE:69FE84FD"},"id":"d62c3197-670e-45d3-9744-befd0023a48b","timestamp":"2026-05-09T00:51:15.454Z","parentId":"bbe7e75b-9bd3-4a97-85d4-76b59771509c"}
